《'''The Best of 2008–2012'''》為香港歌手[[鄧紫棋|鄧紫棋]]推出的首張精選專輯，乃於[[奧地利|奧地利]]壓制，第一版於2013年3月27日發售<ref name="HMV HK">{{Cite web |url=http://www.hmv.com.hk/ch/product/canto.asp?sku=788438 |title=HMV 鄧紫棋 GEM TANG - BEST OF GEM 2008-2012 (2CD) |access-date=2013-07-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924030815/http://www.hmv.com.hk/ch/product/canto.asp?sku=788438 |archive-date=2015-09-24 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。由於反應熱烈，於2013年7月4日推出限量加印版。<ref name="HMV HK 2">{{cite web|title=G.E.M. - The Best Of 2008 - 2012 (2nd Ver)|url=http://www.hmv.com.hk/product/canto.asp?sku=815175|publisher=HMV HK|accessdate=6 May 2016}}{{Dead link|date=2019年10月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
此專輯進入了世界大碟销量周榜第三十九位，成為了首張由中國或香港歌手發行並進入了世界大碟销量周榜的專輯。<ref>[http://www.mediatraffic.de/albums-week11-2014.htm] {{Wayback|url=http://www.mediatraffic.de/albums-week11-2014.htm |date=20140311101730 }} 原文：Nine of this week's 19 debuts and all five new-entries from the track tally are from Asia. It shows how much the influence of this continent has grown. And for the first time in history an album from China (Hong Kong) reaches the Top 40. It's the 'Best Of 2008-2012' by singer G.E.M. and it flies to no.39 with 21.000 copies sold. Congratulations to G.E.M. and to China!!</ref>

